@Luap99 I completely understand (Podman) maintainers aren't interested to maintain and support this Flatpak SDK-extension. I created this issue to notice a Flatpak SDK may be useful, and it already works using `podman-remote`.

In my workflow, I need `podman-remote` to use devcontainers in IDE supported applications (like VSCode). You may even pass flags and uid/gid mapping, `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json`:

```json
{
    "name": "app-devcontainer",
    "containerUser": "docker",
    "containerEnv": {
        "HOME": "/home/docker",
        "CONTAINER_ROLE": "shell"
    },
    "runArgs": ["--network=systemd-myapp", "--init"], // with quadlet networking
    "build": {
        "context": "./../",
        "dockerfile": "./../Containerfile",
        "target": "development"
    }
}
```

This is just an example, I think it can also be useful in other applications that need to interact with containers, while still keeping a sandboxed model, but I do understand not every app can work with this setup.

Please let me know if I should close this issue, the main purpose of this is to make you aware it's possible and interests exists. :)
